{"id": "ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY", "rating": 4.8, "userRatingCount": 232, "displayName": {"text": "House Of Bread", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sweGMyTTBSVUZVVHpBNE0wTmtTM0ppWDFWdFozYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "**4.5/5 🌟🌟🌟🌟✨ House of Bread Westwood: Buttery Croissants Worth the Hunt**\n\nTucked on Westwood Blvd just south of Wilshire, **House of Bread** is the cozy independent bakery that’s been quietly turning out fresh goods for years 🥐❤️. The moment you walk in, the smell of warm dough and real butter hits you—proof everything is baked fresh daily. The display case is modest but tempting: loaves, muffins, and those golden croissants calling your name. The **owner was nice**, chatting with regulars, offering samples, and clearly passionate about the craft.\n\nGot the classic **buttery croissant**, and it delivered on flavor big time. Rich, egg-washed shine on top, soft pull-apart interior with that unmistakable European butter taste—deeply satisfying and not overly sweet. You can tell quality ingredients are used; it’s the kind of croissant that pairs perfectly with coffee or stands alone.\n\nThat said, minor deductions hold it back from perfection. **Flakiness** was good but not shatter-everywhere explosive—some bites were more tender than crisp. The **layers** were visible and tasty, but could use a touch more definition and airiness compared to the absolute top-tier spots. Biggest hassle? **Parking**—Westwood Blvd is a nightmare; metered spots are competitive, and the tiny lot fills instantly. Plan to circle or park a few blocks away.\n\nHouse of Bread isn’t flashy or trendy, but it’s genuinely fresh, owner-operated, and reliably delicious. When that buttery croissant craving hits near UCLA, this is a strong contender. I’ll be back (and leave extra time for parking). Solid neighborhood bakery worth supporting.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "**4.5/5 🌟🌟🌟🌟✨ House of Bread Westwood: Buttery Croissants Worth the Hunt**\n\nTucked on Westwood Blvd just south of Wilshire, **House of Bread** is the cozy independent bakery that’s been quietly turning out fresh goods for years 🥐❤️. The moment you walk in, the smell of warm dough and real butter hits you—proof everything is baked fresh daily. The display case is modest but tempting: loaves, muffins, and those golden croissants calling your name. The **owner was nice**, chatting with regulars, offering samples, and clearly passionate about the craft.\n\nGot the classic **buttery croissant**, and it delivered on flavor big time. Rich, egg-washed shine on top, soft pull-apart interior with that unmistakable European butter taste—deeply satisfying and not overly sweet. You can tell quality ingredients are used; it’s the kind of croissant that pairs perfectly with coffee or stands alone.\n\nThat said, minor deductions hold it back from perfection. **Flakiness** was good but not shatter-everywhere explosive—some bites were more tender than crisp. The **layers** were visible and tasty, but could use a touch more definition and airiness compared to the absolute top-tier spots. Biggest hassle? **Parking**—Westwood Blvd is a nightmare; metered spots are competitive, and the tiny lot fills instantly. Plan to circle or park a few blocks away.\n\nHouse of Bread isn’t flashy or trendy, but it’s genuinely fresh, owner-operated, and reliably delicious. When that buttery croissant craving hits near UCLA, this is a strong contender. I’ll be back (and leave extra time for parking). Solid neighborhood bakery worth supporting.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "James Lin", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110562228716030491265/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgrEU-WxFSgVAjQpeNtdttOn_zcp79kgAeVTU9octSRSF2mPja=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-28T07:01:03.453084343Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sweGMyTTBSVUZVVHpBNE0wTmtTM0ppWDFWdFozYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sweGMyTTBSVUZVVHpBNE0wTmtTM0ppWDFWdFozYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2bb378aa9c3fb:0xa6b6bb7c556a17ed"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sxbmVEWmpXbXgzUjI0NExYTTBiV0l6UVhGYVRGRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 weeks ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "This is exactly how sangak should be! 😍 Fresh out of the oven, crispy, and full of flavor. One of the best I’ve tried. Highly recommend!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "This is exactly how sangak should be! 😍 Fresh out of the oven, crispy, and full of flavor. One of the best I’ve tried. Highly recommend!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "bahareh maghsoudi", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105831384451752750337/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVP-BiAL1lEXd0U8hGJquY7J3PrQMXq3dpisMRZTy4bEoKFo63Z=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"}, "publishTime": "2026-06-16T14:05:16.693288323Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sxbmVEWmpXbXgzUjI0NExYTTBiV0l6UVhGYVRGRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2sxbmVEWmpXbXgzUjI0NExYTTBiV0l6UVhGYVRGRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2bb378aa9c3fb:0xa6b6bb7c556a17ed"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xCbWFVSkNXV3hzZURad1NXdHNOM2hrVG00elpHYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "11 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Excellent place for all bakery products. This always a queue, soliciting the lovely Brazil. I loved the big Sangki bread and the Banana Bread. The hummus and yoghurt dip, what's awesome? It's her secret recipe for over the years. I heard conversations where the third generation had come to buy from the bakery. It is an excellent place to have your morning breakfast and start the day with an excellent taste combined with health. Reasonable prices great value for money", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Excellent place for all bakery products. This always a queue, soliciting the lovely Brazil. I loved the big Sangki bread and the Banana Bread. The hummus and yoghurt dip, what's awesome? It's her secret recipe for over the years. I heard conversations where the third generation had come to buy from the bakery. It is an excellent place to have your morning breakfast and start the day with an excellent taste combined with health. Reasonable prices great value for money", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Dr Mohina S kulkarni", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109705302763826913992/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlBCxjecQNBrpFKIGRt4ugW4DeFhGYp3_5kehFivJUCfS67fQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7"}, "publishTime": "2025-07-26T22:08:09.443221691Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xCbWFVSkNXV3hzZURad1NXdHNOM2hrVG00elpHYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xCbWFVSkNXV3hzZURad1NXdHNOM2hrVG00elpHYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2bb378aa9c3fb:0xa6b6bb7c556a17ed"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURnbjRxYUt3EAE", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I’m in LA for a few months for work, and on my walk to work, I love stopping here and picking up a delicious croissant. I’ve had the almond, cheese, ham & cheese, and plain croissant. Every single one of them is delicious! I can’t wait to try the chocolate croissant. I gobbled down the ham and cheese too quickly to snap a photo but ended up making a heart shape out of the wrapper. 🥐\n\nThe banana bread is also delicious!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I’m in LA for a few months for work, and on my walk to work, I love stopping here and picking up a delicious croissant. I’ve had the almond, cheese, ham & cheese, and plain croissant. Every single one of them is delicious! I can’t wait to try the chocolate croissant. I gobbled down the ham and cheese too quickly to snap a photo but ended up making a heart shape out of the wrapper. 🥐\n\nThe banana bread is also delicious!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Alex", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115097611311292308911/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6NxRzwuPeFe6bVg7XOk8Un_L6whh62-1mwsUe9j9eAwySTtA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2025-02-28T17:39:02.958729Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURnbjRxYUt3EAE&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURnbjRxYUt3EAE!2m1!1s0x80c2bb378aa9c3fb:0xa6b6bb7c556a17ed"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pKemJucFpObFV0VnpGaFNFNVRWRUkzVjJwWE1FRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Everything is amazing, this is the only place around the area where you can buy real bread, loafs, baguettes. It's a rare find. I am not a big fan of flat bread in general but they are famous for their flat bread. Pastries are also amazing! Their home made feta cheese and jams are the best. I am addicted.\nThey are extremely friendly, love the owners. Very cute place and only does window service which makes it very fast. Most of the time there is a line but for a reason. I would highly recommend. I will recommend to go earlier because they can sell out the good stuff fast.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Everything is amazing, this is the only place around the area where you can buy real bread, loafs, baguettes. It's a rare find. I am not a big fan of flat bread in general but they are famous for their flat bread. Pastries are also amazing! Their home made feta cheese and jams are the best. I am addicted.\nThey are extremely friendly, love the owners. Very cute place and only does window service which makes it very fast. Most of the time there is a line but for a reason. I would highly recommend. I will recommend to go earlier because they can sell out the good stuff fast.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Asli Akal", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104230815839787225596/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiib5MKfXrWh-ywsP0Hvjzdz02qFrVObxcxDR8ffN-DgUl0Kwx=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-27T01:44:17.287762643Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pKemJucFpObFV0VnpGaFNFNVRWRUkzVjJwWE1FRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pKemJucFpObFV0VnpGaFNFNVRWRUkzVjJwWE1FRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2bb378aa9c3fb:0xa6b6bb7c556a17ed"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJ-8Opije7woAR7RdqVXy7tqY/photos/AWCwydh7URIZ9A9N6s5hM_5abm2jdIn26XAjd5nWOsE4aEtQxA6S_LNs3Ww3LZRhVkZmjl4HVqPLd1umuAWgrJUaa4zXGz4aMI5bYyEDed88MeNML_IUcHJclk5IqRwBFQ_3WOc8lpQvlkIw0Mik-tmA3-bSILT5KUNrmR3SkI0-Z83HJQjOPrkfTMMMDVDyh3yD2Swyel9c3yvAml6-9EvRw3Ydlj0Lv12f75Klpw3M3iYx9Rk45IeeTDdb9AjlM_brmz2tV1Fj10VpAZ60kmMChK5Z1fxS1J_TBW4NVoyUfrx6o4pH8_Og8LSTpjm7HP-cH8D_0P3f6oj8Z1t3U7JqngomuGqrLRBRqVbhs3GWT9JAD9UmjxIGYo8LIQw4NkLMTuE9G60ZSlbtiOqgCcjRvULAe80L0BHfilOumk08L1RTxFY", "widthPx": 1440, "heightPx": 1800, "authorAttributions": [{"displayName": "Simone Hörster", "uri": "https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/103535193320092240604", "photoUri": "https://lh3